@6013 = ~Dragon Slippers~
@6014 = ~Boots of Speed: Dragon Slippers
These boots were given to Simeon Snowlock upon his passage into manhood, fulfilling the last wish of his great-great-grandfather Prestor John, the first king of the Hayholt. Two years before John had became king, he ventured deep into the underground catacombs beneath his future kingdom, where he came upon a lair so enormous that it could only belong to a creature of gigantic proportions. Drawn by the sight of a thousand riches lining the cave, John stepped forward, and was confronted by monster beyond compare. She was Shurukai, mother of all dragons; and she reached a staggering 25 feet from head to tail, and nearly 50 feet across. Armed with only his with, courage and trusted sword, Brightnail, John swiftly fought a savage battle.
It was rumored that a cataclysmic crash echoed through the entire city, and every man, woman and child ran to see what had become of their most skilled commander. All were awe-struck when they found the red mass collapsed upon the floor, and even more so when John commissioned a throne to be constructed from the bones of the beast, placing the skull upon the highest point. The scales of the beast were removed, and were entwined into a pair of Cheetah's Paws, resulting in footwear that protected the user against fire and morale failure, as well as doubling their movement rate.

Till this day, the throne sits in the centre of the Hayholt for all to admire, its ivory beauty cascading in the sunlight. But mention the name Prestor John, and you will immediately hear the story of Shurakai, and the Dragonbone Chair.

STATISTICS:

