@6045 = ~Messerschmitt Stone Reaver Axe~
@6046 = ~Two Handed Axe +3: Messerschmitt Stone Reaver
The Messerschmitt Stone Reaver Axe combines two popular types of Dwarven axes with an unusual shaft found by an adventuring party. The axe is named after the human Messerschmitt, a rival smith of the craftsman that created this weapon that tried a similar design. The axe fell off his bench and cut off most of his hand. In anger he simply melted the experimental axe down, returned his commission and gave his customer the axes in a hot ladle full of slagged iron & mithril. Messerschmitt explained the Gods were punishing him for taking two fine, Dwarven axes and making such an abomination for a Halfling. The Halfling promptly kicked Messerschmitt in the shins and stormed out.

The design is a double headed axe with Stone Fire on one side and Frost Reaver on the other. Both of these axes had to be reforged to make them large enough to make this fearsome two handed, double headed axe but they have lost none of their potency. The damage that is done to the target depends greatly on which side of the axe they are hit with. Upon completion of the axe, it's user was very clear that the axe may be be cursed and never let a Halfling wield it. The same is probably true for Gnomes as well. The weapon's creator hinted at some special protective magic to ensure just such a case. "Wouldn't want this weapon to fall into either the wrong, or small, hands", he said.

This design has obvious merits for use against trolls and the unusual staff has given it the ability to kill fire elementals in a single strike. Properly used, it can block weapon strikes as well. The axe is so heavy at the ends, it is an excellent weapon against armored opponents as it cleaves through armor, piercing instead of slashing. So deeply can it bite that sometimes it is hard to pull out of an opponent.

